Maven Java Web Application: CI/CD Pipeline to Tomcat

Overview
Java web application built with Maven. Originally created 4 years ago in 2022 and modernized in 2026. Demonstrates an automated CI/CD pipeline from source control to deployment on Apache Tomcat.

Tech Stack
Language: Java JDK 21 LTS
Build Tool: Apache Maven 3.9.6
CI/CD: Jenkins
Code Quality: SonarQube 2026.1 LTA
Deployment: Apache Tomcat 10.1
Containerization: Docker
Infrastructure: AWS EC2 or Amazon EKS

Pipeline Evolution
2022: Initial implementation using Maven 3.8.6, Tomcat 9 deploy plugin. Original repository: maven-web-application.git--jenks
2026: Modernized to Maven 3.9.6, Tomcat 10.1 Manager API, Jakarta EE compatible. Repository: java-cicd-jenkins-sonar

Pipeline Workflow
Commit: Code pushed to GitHub triggers Jenkins via webhook
Build: Maven runs unit tests and packages .war artifact with mvn clean package
Analysis: SonarQube performs static application security testing and quality gate check
Containerization: Docker multi-stage build packages .war with Tomcat 10.1
Deployment: Container deployed to Tomcat on AWS

Files
Jenkinsfile: Current 2026 pipeline
Jenkinsfile.2022: Original 2022 pipeline

Getting Started

Prerequisites
JDK 21
Maven 3.9.6
Docker Desktop

Build Locally
git clone github.com
cd java-cicd-jenkins-sonar
mvn clean package

Artifact is generated in /target directory.

Run with Docker
docker build -t maven-web-app:v2 .
docker run -p 8080:8080 maven-web-app:v2

Application deploys to Tomcat and is accessible at localhost:8080

